let's review the fraction addition approach first. The first must have the smallest denominators. Thus, evaluating the addition of the following fraction: $\left(\dfrac{1}{4} + \dfrac{1}{5}\right)$ must give us the smallest sum:

\begin{align}
\dfrac{1}{4}+\dfrac{1}{5}\\
= \dfrac{1\times5}{20}+\dfrac{1\times4}{20}\\
=\dfrac{15}{20}+\dfrac{16}{20}\\
=\dfrac{31}{20}\\
=\boxed{\dfrac{31}{20}}\end{align}

Thus, the answer is $\boxed{\dfrac{31}{20}}$.

